snippet.textDisplay: i love dnd and i love the try guys so i thought i would love this but, it was horrible i could barely watch it and i am not blaming the guys as its their first session at least in many years and seeing them roleplaying as they did was nice as most new players don't  and it is fine that their characters are a bit one dimensional . now the problem was the dm and the editing , i havent been playing/ dming for long but to me his storytelling is a bit clunky and he kept saying that the characters did something  that they didnt say they wanted to do and them telling them to roll checks and just because it is their first session  doesnt mean it has to be boring . now the  editing it kept not showing  them using spells are actually saying they do the action  also it feels like the guys have less than basic understanding of the game and as dm it is his job to not let that happen  and you know tell them how it works  and explain completely and answer all their questions  but in the end all that matters is that the guys had fun because that is what dnd is about
snippet.textOriginal: i love dnd and i love the try guys so i thought i would love this but, it was horrible i could barely watch it and i am not blaming the guys as its their first session at least in many years and seeing them roleplaying as they did was nice as most new players don't  and it is fine that their characters are a bit one dimensional . now the problem was the dm and the editing , i havent been playing/ dming for long but to me his storytelling is a bit clunky and he kept saying that the characters did something  that they didnt say they wanted to do and them telling them to roll checks and just because it is their first session  doesnt mean it has to be boring . now the  editing it kept not showing  them using spells are actually saying they do the action  also it feels like the guys have less than basic understanding of the game and as dm it is his job to not let that happen  and you know tell them how it works  and explain completely and answer all their questions  but in the end all that matters is that the guys had fun because that is what dnd is about
